  "dateModified": "2026-03-31",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-31",
  "description": "Genring — the reduction of a living people to a fixed literary type — is a political operation traceable from Herder's Volksgeist through the Brothers Grimm to Karl May and Oktoberfest. Fascist exclusion follows from genre coherence: once a nation accepts a fixed cast of folk types, anyone who deviates becomes a threat to the story.",
  "name": "The Reduction of a People to a Type: Genring, Romantic Nationalism, and the Mechanics of Fascist Exclusion",
